<section class="ch-parent" id="parents">
  <div class="parent-grid">
    <div class="parent-text reveal">
      <div class="eyebrow">For parents</div>
      <h2 class="h2">
        <span class="serif-it">Observation</span>, not direction.
      </h2>
      <p>
        The player holds the toggles. <strong>Not the parent. Not the coach.</strong>
      </p>
      <p>
        A youth product only earns its place at the family table if the kid has the controls.
        Composed gives the player three switches — ratings, coach feedback, development goals — and the parent dashboard shows only what's been turned on.
      </p>
      <p>
        Video is compressed and frame-extracted <strong>on the phone</strong> before upload. The analysis model sees counts — shots, passes, foot usage — <strong>not faces or locations</strong>. Raw footage is discarded once the stats come back.
      </p>
      <p>
        Coaches stay coaches. Parents stay supportive. The training conversation stays inside the app.
      </p>
      <div class="closer">
        The parent sees what the player <strong>allows them</strong> to see — not the other way around.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="reveal" aria-hidden="true">
      <div class="toggles-card">
        <div class="toggles-title">Privacy · player controls</div>
        <div class="toggles-sub">parent_visibility_settings</div>
        <div class="toggle-row">
          <span class="toggle-name">Share ratings</span>
          <span class="toggle-switch on" role="img" aria-label="On"></span>
        </div>
        <div class="toggle-row">
          <span class="toggle-name">Share coach feedback</span>
          <span class="toggle-switch on" role="img" aria-label="On"></span>
        </div>
        <div class="toggle-row">
          <span class="toggle-name">Share development goals</span>
          <span class="toggle-switch" role="img" aria-label="Off"></span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

